The article criticizes Bernie Sanders' healthcare bill, stating that it would take away healthcare choices from patients and hurt seniors. It argues that the bill would eliminate private health insurance for almost 180 million Americans and wipe out Medicare Advantage for over 22 million people. It also claims that the bill would harm the economy and provide free care to illegal immigrants. The estimated cost of the bill is stated to be over $32 trillion over the next 10 years. The article further argues that the bill would abolish support for military families and the Children's Health Insurance Program (CHIP). It concludes by stating that instead of reshaping the economy, efforts should be made to reduce healthcare costs and improve existing systems.